23/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase said Friday (21 November) that the opposition must be more flexible when discussing the upcoming elections. 
Otherwise, he said, the government will make a decision on its own concerning the timing of the vote.His statement came after the opposition rejected government proposals. 
The Liberals and Democrats have threatened to leave parliament if the ruling party does not give up plans to hold local and parliamentary elections at the same time, in June 2004. 
(Nine O'clock - 21/11/03)
